'''聖安東尼奧河'''（{{lang-en|San Antonio River}}）是[[美國|美國]][[德克薩斯州|德克薩斯州]]中南部河流，亦是{{tsl|en|Guadalupe River (Texas)|瓜達盧普河 (德克薩斯州)|瓜達盧普河}}支流，全長約390公里，流域面積約10,880平方公里。河流源自[[圣安东尼奥_(得克萨斯州)|圣安东尼奥]]水泉，主要往东南流動，流經[[弗洛爾斯維爾_(德克薩斯州)|弗洛爾斯維爾]]及[[戈利亚德_(得克萨斯州)|戈利亚德]]等城鎮，最終在提弗利北部與瓜達盧普河合流。早在[[西班牙帝國|西班牙帝國]]殖民美洲之前，河流流域乃至德州中南部地區已有[[美洲原住民|美洲原住民]]居住。後來歐洲各國探險家先後路經河流，它亦因而有著不同名稱。現時河流的名稱源自1691年，得名於天主教紀念日[[羅馬天主教聖人曆|聖安多尼瞻禮日]]。18世紀初，西班牙人在河流源頭一帶建立永久聚落及多個傳教站，但在這些傳教站最終因[[世俗化|世俗化]]而於世紀末被棄置，或轉為自治的原住民村落。在[[得克萨斯革命|得克萨斯革命]]期間，河流一帶爆發先後爆發多場戰役，其中以[[阿拉摩之戰|阿拉摩之戰]]最為慘烈。

河流流域生態多樣，孕育着不少動植物，其中更包括數種受威脅物種。但是，流域同時亦遭受[[入侵物種|入侵物種]]侵-{}-襲，而它們更會對原生物種乃至生態系統造成嚴重威脅。河流發生多次洪災，其中1921年的洪災更促使聖安東尼奧市進行河道截斷工程及修建水壩下水道等防洪設施，而及後成為市內景點的{{tsl|en|San Antonio River Walk|聖安東尼奧河濱步道}}亦應運而生。數十年後，[[美國陸軍工程兵團|美國陸軍工程兵團]]與聖安東尼奧河管理局合作，先後進行河流渠道化、改善水壩及修建地下泄洪隧道等工程，強化河流的防洪能力。流域內設有多個休閒設施，除了河濱步道外，多個經修復的傳教站亦是著名景點，而其中五個傳教站及相關建築更於2015年被[[聯合國教科文組織|聯合國教科文組織]]列入[[世界遺產|世界遺產]]。

== 流向 ==
[[File:San_Antonio_Riverwalk_(2013)_IMG_7600.JPG|thumb]]
聖安東尼奧河發源於[[圣安东尼奥_(得克萨斯州)|聖安東尼奧]]內的{{tsl|en|San Antonio Springs|聖安東尼奧泉}}<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv">{{Cite web |url = https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/san-antonio-river |title = San Antonio River |last = Donecker |first = Frances |publisher = Texas State Historical Association |language = en |accessdate = 2021-01-31 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210131112138/https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/san-antonio-river |archivedate = 2021-01-31}}</ref>{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}。基於防洪原因，市內河段大多被混凝土河道取代，但有部份河段仍保留自然風貌<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv" />。河流在奧爾莫斯公園附近與奧爾莫斯溪（{{lang|en|Olmos Creek}}）合流後，會往西南方向流動，並流經{{tsl|en|San Antonio Zoo|聖安東尼奧動物園}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1973|pp=35-37}}。離開動物園後，河流會先後流經兩個防洪建築物，並在康塞普西翁公園附近與聖佩德羅溪（{{lang|en|San Pedro Creek}}）合流<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv" /><ref name="WCRP@CreekwaysTrail">{{Cite web |url = https://www.westsidecreeks.com/apachesan-pedro-creekways-trail-progress/ |title = Apache/San Pedro Creekways Trail Progress |author = Westside Creeks Restoration Project |publisher = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201026162252/https://www.westsidecreeks.com/apachesan-pedro-creekways-trail-progress/ |archivedate = 2020-10-26}}</ref>。此時，河流將會改往東南方流動，並在[[史汀森市立機場|史汀森市立機場]]東北方流經埃斯帕達水壩（Espada Dam）<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv" /><ref name"NPS@EspadaDam">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nps.gov/places/espada-dam.htm |title = Espada Dam |author = National Park Service |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-01 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210201124113/https://www.nps.gov/places/espada-dam.htm |archivedate = 2021-02-01}}</ref>。到達城市邊緣後，河流會在{{tsl|en|Victor Braunig Lake|維克多·布勞尼格湖}}東南方與{{tsl|en|Medina River|梅迪納河}}匯合{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1954|pp=15-16}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1973|pp=35-37}}。

離開聖安東尼奧後，河流開始以較為曲折的路線流動。流經{{tsl|en|Calaveras, Texas|卡拉維拉斯 (德克薩斯州)|卡拉維拉斯}}後，河流會在[[弗洛爾斯維爾_(德克薩斯州)|弗洛爾斯維爾]]西北方與凱斯特溪（{{lang|en|Kicaster Creek}}）匯合{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1973|pp=35-37}}。接著，河流會繼續往東南方流動，先後流經{{tsl|en|Poth, Texas|波思 (德克薩斯州)|波思}}及{{tsl|en|Falls City, Texas|福爾斯城 (得克萨斯州)|福爾斯城}}，並在福爾斯城東部與馬塞利納斯溪（{{lang|en|Marcelina Creek}}）匯合{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1973|pp=35-37}}。之後，河流又會流經{{tsl|en|Hobson, Texas|霍布森 (得克萨斯州)|霍布森}}及{{tsl|en|Panna Maria, Texas|潘納瑪麗亞 (得克萨斯州)|潘納瑪麗亞}}等地，並在[[鬼鎮|鬼鎮]]{{tsl|en|Helena, Texas|海倫娜 (德克薩斯州)|海倫娜}}附近與[[席博羅溪|席博羅溪]]合流{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1973|pp=35-37}}。及後，河流會先後穿越80號、72號、239號及59號德克薩斯州州道，並流經[[戈利亚德_(得克萨斯州)|戈利亚德]]南部的{{tsl|en|Goliad State Park and Historic Site|戈利亞德州立公園及歷史遺址}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1954|pp=15-16}}{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1973|pp=35-37}}。河流在離開公園後繼續往東南方流動，而河道則在洛特湖（{{lang|en|Lott Lake}}）東部再次變得曲折蜿蜒，最終在{{tsl|en|Tivoli, Texas|提弗利 (得克萨斯州)|提弗利}}北部與{{tsl|en|Guadalupe River (Texas)|瓜達盧普河 (德克薩斯州)|瓜達盧普河}}匯合<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv" />{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=20}}。

== 流域 ==
聖安東尼奧河的流域面積約為10,880平方公里（4,180平方英里），橫跨[[比爾縣|比爾縣]]、[[威爾遜縣_(德克薩斯州)|威爾遜縣]]、[[卡恩斯縣_(德克薩斯州)|卡恩斯縣]]、[[戈利亞德縣_(德克薩斯州)|戈利亞德縣]]及[[里菲吉奧縣_(德克薩斯州)|里菲吉奧縣]]<ref name="USACE-FWD_FactSheet"/><ref name="SARAreport2018">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/sites/default/files/wp-documents/2018-CRP-Report-Full-web.pdf |title = San Antonio River Basin 2018 Summary Report |author = San Antonio River Authority |year = 2018 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-01-31 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210131142022/https://www.sariverauthority.org/sites/default/files/wp-documents/2018-CRP-Report-Full-web.pdf |archivedate = 2021-01-31}}</ref>。流域內共有數條主要支流，包括{{tsl|en|Medina River|梅迪納河}}、薩拉多溪（{{lang|en|Salado Creek}}）及[[席博羅溪|席博羅溪]]等，而這些河溪流域則與聖安東尼奧河流域共同組成聖安東尼奧河盆地<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。盆地位於德州中南部，始於[[班德拉縣|班德拉縣]]的東北部，終於戈利亞德縣<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。流域海拔範圍由1至760米（3至2,500英尺），最低點是河口，而最高點則是位於班德拉縣及克爾縣的德克薩斯州丘陵地區<ref name="San Antonio River Facts">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/education/san-antonio-river-basin |title = The San Antonio River Basin |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-03 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201201013025/https://www.sariverauthority.org/education/san-antonio-river-basin |archivedate = 2020-12-01}}</ref>。流域屬於[[副熱帶濕潤氣候|副熱帶濕潤氣候]]，夏季炎熱多雨，冬季溫和乾燥<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。流域的年平均降雨量約為660至970毫米（26至38英寸），五月和十月的降雨量會稍為增多<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref>{{Cite journal|title=Effects of Urbanization and Climate Change on Hydrological Processes over the San Antonio River Basin, Texas|url=https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2014AGUFM.H31H0714Z/abstract|last=Zhao|first=G.|last2=Gao|first2=H.|date=2014-12-XX|journal=AGU Fall Meeting Abstracts|volume=2014|pages=H31H–0714|language=en|last3=Cuo|first3=L.|access-date=2021-05-03|archive-date=2021-05-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210503094547/https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2014AGUFM.H31H0714Z/abstract|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在土地用途方面，上游流域以已發展地區、牧場及灌木叢為主，而下游流域則以農業和牧場為主<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。人口數據方面，[[美國普查局|美國普查局]]曾在2002年估計比爾縣人口約有140萬人，而2016年數字則升至約190萬人，升幅達36%<ref name="Ockerman & McNamara, 2003">{{Cite web |url = https://pubs.usgs.gov/wri/wri03-4030/pdf/wri03-4030.pdf |title = Simulation of Streamflow and Estimation of Streamflow Constituent Loads in the San Antonio River Watershed, Bexar County, Texas, 1997-2001 |last1 = Ockerman |first1 = Darwin J. |last2 = McNamara |first2 = Kenna C. |year = 2003 |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-04-03 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190430014242/https://pubs.usgs.gov/wri/wri03-4030/pdf/wri03-4030.pdf |archivedate = 2019-04-30}}</ref><ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。[[圣安东尼奥_(得克萨斯州)|聖安東尼奧]]是上游流域內最大的城市，根據2016年美國人口普查，該市約有150萬人口<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。雖然下游流域同樣有[[人口中心|人口中心]]，但只佔整體4.7%<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。

== 地理 ==
大約在1.4億年前的白堊紀早期，中生代淺海覆蓋德克薩斯州大部份地區，最終向西延伸至[[跨佩科斯區域|跨佩科斯區域]]，及向北延伸至現時的州界<ref name="TX_Geology">{{Cite web |url = https://texasalmanac.com/topics/environment/geology-texas-0 |title = Geology of Texas |author = Texas Almanac |publisher = Texas State Historical Association |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201121104703/https://texasalmanac.com/topics/environment/geology-texas-0 |archivedate = 2020-11-21}}</ref>。許多類型的動物（例如[[珊瑚|珊瑚]]、[[蛤蜊|蛤蜊]]及[[貽貝|貽貝]]）生活在中生代淺海、潮汐池和沿海沼澤內<ref name="TX_Geology"/><ref name="SAEN@GeologyHistory">{{Cite web |url = https://www.expressnews.com/news/local/history-culture/article/Geology-guided-San-Antonio-s-history-11044229.php |title = Geology guided San Antonio’s history |last = Gibbons |first = Brendan |date = 2017-04-02 |publisher = San Antonio Express-News |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811014655/https://www.expressnews.com/news/local/history-culture/article/Geology-guided-San-Antonio-s-history-11044229.php |archivedate = 2020-08-11}}</ref>。而大約在1.2億年前，中生代淺海床的土壤與動物殘骸混合，形成[[遠海沉積物#鈣質軟泥|鈣質軟泥]]，最終埋入較年輕的地層下並形成石灰岩<ref name="SAEN@GeologyHistory"/><ref name="CentralTexasGeology">{{Cite web |url = http://communitycircular.com/articles/geology-of-central-texas.htm |title = The Geology of Central Texas and Its Present Day Wonders |last = Marx |first = Susan |publisher = Community Circular |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190911075512/http://www.communitycircular.com/articles/geology-of-central-texas.htm |archivedate = 2019-09-11}}</ref>。現時，這些沉積在淺海的石灰岩暴露在流經{{tsl|en|Edwards Plateau|愛德華茲高原}}的河溪源頭及流域內，以及聖安東尼奧至[[達拉斯|達拉斯]]的德州中部地區，而土壤亦富含無數代動植物的有機物<ref name="TX_Geology"/>。另外，{{tsl|en|Austin Chalk|奧斯汀白堊岩}}是區內其中一組較著名的岩石地層，它自鄰近[[伊格爾帕斯_(德克薩斯州)|伊格爾帕斯]]的[[格蘭德河|格蘭德河]]延伸，東至聖安東尼奧，北至達拉斯一帶<ref name="TX_Geology"/>。在[[第三紀|第三紀]]時期，{{tsl|en|Balcones Fault|巴爾科內斯斷層帶}}形成，破壞從愛德華茲高原流入平原的{{tsl|en|Edwards Aquifer|愛德華茲含水層}}，並基於湧泉壓力而把大量水壓向地表<ref name="CentralTexasGeology"/>{{sfn|Sharp Jr.|Green|Schindel|2019|pp=9-18}}。斷層帶形成了許多水泉，例如聖佩德羅泉、聖馬科斯泉、巴頓泉及薩拉多泉等，為流域一帶居民提供淡水資源<ref name="CentralTexasGeology"/>{{sfn|Sharp Jr.|Green|Schindel|2019|pp=9-18}}。此外，聖安東尼奧亦是其中一個位於該斷層帶的城市<ref name="CentralTexasGeology"/>{{sfn|Sharp Jr.|Green|Schindel|2019|pp=9-18}}。

== 水文與污染 ==
聖安東尼奧河流域主要的水流量源自愛德華茲-聖三一含水層系統（{{lang|en|Edwards-Trinity Aquifer System}}）<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。愛德華茲高原上的降雨流經地表後會進入附近河溪，而隨著河溪穿過巴爾科內斯斷層帶，水會流進含水層系統並為其帶來補給<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref name="WaterResourcesReport1995">{{Cite web |url = https://pubs.usgs.gov/wri/1995/4186/report.pdf |title = Geology and Hydrology of the Edwards Aquifer in the San Antonio Area, Texas |last = Maclay |first = Robert W. |year = 1995 |publisher = U.S. Grological Survey |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170303113741/https://pubs.usgs.gov/wri/1995/4186/report.pdf |archivedate = 2017-03-03}}</ref>。根據估計，每年約有783,900,000立方米（635,500英畝·英尺）的水量經{{tsl|en|Infiltration (hydrology)|下滲作用}}流入該含水層系統<ref name="WaterResourcesReport1995"/>。該含水層除了是大量天然水泉的源頭外，亦為聖安東尼奧市提供大約90%的飲用水及70%的市政用水<ref name="TexasAquifers">{{Cite web |url = https://texasalmanac.com/topics/environment/aquifers-texas |title = Aquifers of Texas |author = Texas Almanac |publisher = Texas State Historical Association |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210117195652/https://texasalmanac.com/topics/environment/aquifers-texas |archivedate = 2021-01-17}}</ref>。然而，河流的基本流量主要是依賴聖安東尼奧動物園的井水排放及水力公司聖安東尼奧供水系統（{{lang|en|San Antonio Water System}}）處理後所得的[[再生水|再生水]]<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。如果沒有這種額外的水流，河流流量將會進一步減低，導致溶解氧下降並損害生物群落，而在乾旱期間更會導致部份河溪水位下降甚至乾涸<ref name="NPR@111001">{{Cite web |url = https://www.npr.org/2011/10/01/140937267/recycled-water-quenches-san-antonios-thirst |title = Recycled Water Quenches San Antonio's Thirst |last = Goodwyn |first = Wade |date = 2011-10-01 |publisher = NPR |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210202095743/https://www.npr.org/2011/10/01/140937267/recycled-water-quenches-san-antonios-thirst |archivedate = 2021-02-02}}</ref><ref name="SAWS_RecycledWater">{{Cite web |url = https://www.saws.org/your-water/new-water-sources/current-water-supply-projects/recycled-water/ |title = Irrigational & Industrial Recycled Water: An Environmentally Responsible, Cost-Effective Alternative |author = San Antonio Water System |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201213174709/https://www.saws.org/your-water/new-water-sources/current-water-supply-projects/recycled-water/ |archivedate = 2020-12-13}}</ref>。另外，該公司在聖安東尼奧市及周邊地區排出的再生水亦為[[比爾縣|比爾縣]]之後的河段提供大量水流<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。除了愛德華茲-聖三一含水層系統外，河流流域亦橫跨{{tsl|en|Carrizo-Wilcox Aquifer|卡里佐-維爾科克斯含水層}}及墨西哥灣沿岸含水層（{{lang|en|Gulf Coast Aquifer}}），而它們則為其他位於中下游流域的支流補給或提供水流量<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。另外，卡里佐-維爾科克斯含水層還為[[威爾遜縣_(德克薩斯州)|威爾遜縣]]及比爾縣部份地區提供水源，而墨西哥灣沿岸含水層則為[[卡恩斯縣_(德克薩斯州)|卡恩斯縣]]及[[戈利亞德縣_(德克薩斯州)|戈利亞德縣]]提供水源<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。

{{tsl|en|Texas Commission on Environmental Quality|德克薩斯州環境質量委員會}}（TCEQ）會每兩年進行一次水體評估，以滿足《{{tsl|en|Clean Water Act|淨水法}}》的要求。2000年，TCEQ確認聖安東尼奧河及其支流薩拉多溪因細菌而受損，並把它們列入德克薩斯州水質清單內<ref name="TMDL2007">{{Cite web |url = https://www.tceq.texas.gov/assets/public/waterquality/tmdl/34uppersa/34-uppersanantoniotmdl-adopted.pdf |title = Three Total Maximum Daily Loads for Bacteria in the San Antonio Area |author = Texas Commission on Environmental Quality |date = 2007-07-25 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190907173609/https://www.tceq.texas.gov/assets/public/waterquality/tmdl/34uppersa/34-uppersanantoniotmdl-adopted.pdf |archivedate = 2019-09-07}}</ref>。2002年，另一條溪流亦因同樣理由而被列入清單<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref name="TMDL2007"/>。2007年，TCEQ根據《淨水法》來設立{{tsl|en|Total maximum daily load|總最大日負荷}}（TMDL），訂立在滿足水質標準的同時水體可以接受的最大污染物量，而美國國家環境保護局亦在同年批准設立TMDL<ref name="TMDL2007"/>。同時，TCEQ在TMDL報告內亦提及可能的污染源，包括：廢水處理設施和其他機構的排放，城市雨水排放系統的排放，未開發土地的徑流，野生動物、牲畜和寵物的排泄，下水道設施洩漏，以及化糞池系統故障<ref name="TMDL2007"/>。另外在2018年，根據聖安東尼奧河管理局發表的《清潔河流報告》，細菌仍是河流流域最大的單一污染問題<ref name="Gibbons@SAR_180830">{{Cite web |url = https://sanantonioreport.org/bacteria-pollution-makes-san-antonio-creeks-rivers-not-swimmable/ |title = Bacterial Pollution Makes San Antonio Creeks and Rivers Not Swimmable |last = Gibbons |first = Brendan |date = 2018-08-30 |publisher = San Antonio Report |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201028054637/https://sanantonioreport.org/bacteria-pollution-makes-san-antonio-creeks-rivers-not-swimmable/ |archivedate = 2020-10-28}}</ref>。問題在暴雨侵襲期間變得嚴重，河溪的大腸桿菌含量在暴雨過後一度急升200%以上，達到每100毫升460個大腸桿菌，遠超德州標準每100毫升126個大腸桿菌的三倍半<ref name="Gibbons@SAR_180830"/>。同時，總部位於奧斯汀的環保組織「環境德克薩斯」（{{lang|en|Environment Texas}}）亦發表報告，指聖安東尼奧河沿岸的幾個熱門地點都發現{{tsl|en|Fecal coliform|糞便型大腸菌類}}，以及有多個地點都不適合游泳<ref name="Chapa@SABJ_180830">{{Cite web |url = https://www.bizjournals.com/sanantonio/news/2018/08/30/report-unsafe-bacteria-levels-detected-at-several.html |title = Unsafe bacteria levels detected at several popular spots along San Antonio River |last = Chapa |first = Sergio |date = 2018-08-30 |publisher = San Antonio Business Journal |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210202132350/https://www.bizjournals.com/sanantonio/news/2018/08/30/report-unsafe-bacteria-levels-detected-at-several.html |archivedate = 2021-02-02}}</ref>。

== 生態 ==
[[File:Rotundaria_aurea.jpg|thumb]]
在德克薩斯州南部，聖安東尼奧河流域是其中一個生態多樣的地區，橫跨{{tsl|en|Texas Hill Country|德克薩斯州丘陵地區}}、波斯特橡樹草原（{{lang|en|Post Oak Savannah}}）、黑地草原（{{lang|en|Blackland Prairie}}）、德克薩斯州南部平原（{{lang|en|South Texas Plains}}）、墨西哥灣沿岸草原和沼澤（{{lang|en|Gulf Coast Prairies and Marshes}}）五個[[生態區|生態區]]<ref name="Yi, et.al@2017">{{Cite journal |last1 = Yi |first1 = Hoonchong |last2 = Güneralp |first2 = Burak |last3 = Filippi |first3 = Anthony M. |last4 = Kreuter |first4 = Urs P. |last5 = Güneralp‬ |first5 = İnci |url = https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0921800916306899 |title = Impacts of Land Change on Ecosystem Services in the San Antonio River Basin, Texas, from 1984 to 2010 |journal = Ecological Economics |year = 2017 |volume = 135 |pages = 125-135 |access-date = 2021-02-12 |archive-date = 2020-06-22 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200622111341/https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0921800916306899 |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="SARA_Ecoregions">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/ecosystems/ecosystems-san-antonio-river-watershed |title = Ecoregions of the San Antonio River Watershed |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-04 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201129233710/https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/ecosystems/ecosystems-san-antonio-river-watershed |archivedate = 2020-11-29}}</ref>。這數個生態區的植物群落均以[[草本植物|草本植物]]為主，而[[木本植物|木本植物]]的數量則較少，整個流域常綠林及混合林的所佔比率不足5%<ref name="SARAreport2018"/>。流域的常見植物包括[[刺柏|刺柏]]、[[橡樹|橡樹]]、{{tsl|en|Mesquite|牧豆樹}}、相思樹、[[長山核桃|長山核桃]]、{{tsl|en|Andropogon gerardi|大須芒草}}、{{tsl|en|Sorghastrum nutans|印第安草}}、{{tsl|en|Liatris|麒麟菊}}、[[風箱樹|風箱樹]]及食用仙人掌等<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref name="SARA_Ecoregions"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.nps.gov/saan/learn/nature/plants.htm |title = San Antonio Missions National Historical Park - Plants |author = National Park Service |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-04 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809202858/https://www.nps.gov/saan/learn/nature/plants.htm |archivedate = 2020-08-09}}</ref><ref name="Flora&Fauna">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sanantonio.gov/Remember-the-River/Get-the-Facts/Water-Facts-and-Impacts |title = Water Facts & Impacts |author = City of San Antonio |date = 2014 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-04 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210118081048/https://www.sanantonio.gov/Remember-the-River/Get-the-Facts/Water-Facts-and-Impacts |archivedate = 2021-01-18}}</ref>。[[石茅|石茅]]是流域內常見的[[入侵物種|入侵植物]]，它能以[[自花授粉|自花授粉]]的形式快速繁殖下一代，在單個季節中每株植物甚至可產生最多8萬粒種子{{sfn|White|2013|pp=16-17}}<ref name="Klein&Smith2020">{{Cite journal |last1 = Klein |first1 = Peter |last2 = Smith |first2 = Charles Michael |url = https://link.springer.com/article/10.2478/s11756-020-00625-5 |title = Invasive Johnsongrass, a threat to native grasslands and agriculture |journal = Biologia |year = 2020 |volume = 76 |pages = 413-420 |access-date = 2021-02-12 |archive-date = 2021-04-29 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210429055840/https://link.springer.com/article/10.2478/s11756-020-00625-5 |dead-url = no }}</ref>。另外，多功能的根莖及對競爭植物的化感作用亦有助石茅提高競爭力及入侵性，從而改變當地的土壤生物化學及降低草原上原生植物多樣性<ref name="Klein&Smith2020"/>。如果缺乏有效控制，石茅的密度將會大幅增加，同時影響當地農作物收成<ref name="Klein&Smith2020"/>。

聖安東尼奧河是不少動物的棲息地。流域內常見的兩棲動物包括{{tsl|en|Comal blind salamander|科馬爾盲螈}}、[[美国牛蛙|美国牛蛙]]、[[里奧格蘭德豹蛙|里奧格蘭德豹蛙]]、{{tsl|en|Nerodia rhombifer|環紋游蛇}}、[[擬鱷龜|擬鱷龜]]及[[紅耳龜|紅耳龜]]等，而哺乳動物則包括[[浣熊|浣熊]]、[[白尾鹿|白尾鹿]]、[[九帶犰狳|九帶犰狳]]、[[東部棉尾兔|東部棉尾兔]]、[[領西貒|領西貒]]、負鼠及[[郊狼|郊狼]]等<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref name="Flora&Fauna"/>。另外，常見魚類包括[[大口黑鱸|大口黑鱸]]、[[鏟鮰|鏟鮰]]、[[長耳太陽魚|長耳太陽魚]]及[[钳鱼|钳鱼]]等<ref name="Flora&Fauna"/>。[[河岸濕地|河岸濕地]]以及聖安東尼奧市內的綠道和公園亦吸引不少林地鳥種和候鳥棲息，包括[[火雞|火雞]]、[[鵪鶉|鵪鶉]]、[[鴿子|鴿子]]、[[蒼鷺|蒼鷺]]、[[鳴禽|鳴禽]]、[[角鸕鶿|角鸕鶿]]、[[綠頭鴨|綠頭鴨]]及[[魚鷹|魚鷹]]等<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref name="Flora&Fauna"/>。除此之外，瀕危的[[美洲鶴|美洲鶴]]及[[奧氏角雉|奧氏角雉]]亦在墨西哥灣沿岸草原和沼澤生態區一帶棲息<ref name="SARA_Ecoregions"/>。2017年，聖安東尼奧河管理局的生物學家完成針對整個流域的調查，發現約12種淡水貽貝物種，其中包括只在德州棲息且屬於[[受威脅物種|受威脅物種]]的''Rotundaria aurea''<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2011/10/06/2011-25471/endangered-and-threatened-wildlife-and-plants-12-month-finding-on-a-petition-to-list-texas-fatmucket#p-50 |title = Endangered and Threatened Wildlife and Plants; 12-Month Finding on a Petition To List Texas Fatmucket, Golden Orb, Smooth Pimpleback, Texas Pimpleback, and Texas Fawnsfoot as Threatened or Endangered |author = U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service |date = 2011-10-06 |publisher = Federal Register |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-04 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029082614/https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2011/10/06/2011-25471/endangered-and-threatened-wildlife-and-plants-12-month-finding-on-a-petition-to-list-texas-fatmucket |archivedate = 2020-10-29}}</ref>。流域內常見的入侵動物包括[[斑馬貽貝|斑馬貽貝]]、[[福壽螺|福壽螺]]及[[罗非鱼|罗非鱼]]等<ref name="SARAreport2018"/><ref name="Boes@SpectrumNews_200109">{{Cite web |url = https://spectrumlocalnews.com/tx/san-antonio/news/2020/01/09/invasive-snails-being-removed-from-san-antonio-river-walk |title = Invasive Snails Being Removed from San Antonio River Walk |last = Boes |first = Bryan |date = 2020-01-09 |publisher = Spectrum News 1 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-04 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200110234052/https://spectrumlocalnews.com/tx/san-antonio/news/2020/01/09/invasive-snails-being-removed-from-san-antonio-river-walk |archivedate = 2020-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.mysanantonio.com/lifestyle/travel-outdoors/article/Invasive-tilapia-is-taking-over-Texas-waters-15089443.php |title = Invasive tilapia are taking over Texas waters, including two San Antonio lakes |last = Aguirre |first = Priscilla |date = 2020-02-27 |publisher = mysanantonio.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-04 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200404152701/https://www.mysanantonio.com/lifestyle/travel-outdoors/article/Invasive-tilapia-is-taking-over-Texas-waters-15089443.php |archivedate = 2020-04-04}}</ref>。以福壽螺為例，它會吃掉大量水中植物來改變河道及濕地的植物群落結構，降低自然水生植物的密度並使河水變得渾濁，甚至會與本土物種競爭間接改變底棲生物群落結構<ref>{{Cite journal |last1 = Horgan |first1 = Finbarr G. |last2 = Stuart |first2 = Alexander M. |last3 = Kudavidanage |first3 = Enoka P. |title = Impact of invasive apple snails on the functioning and services of natural and managed wetlands |journal = Acta Oecologica |year = 2014 |volume = 54 |pages = 90-100}}</ref>。

== 歷史 ==
=== 17世紀以前 ===
