早在一萬多年前，德克薩斯中南部地區已經是[[美洲原住民|美洲原住民]]的居住地{{sfn|Newcomb, Jr.|1961|pp=54-55}}{{sfn|Raycraft|Beckett|2006|p=7}}<ref name="Barnett@Post_160310">{{Cite web |url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/travel/san-antonio-missions-preserve-native-american-history-at-the-nations-newest-world-heritage-site/2016/03/10/69356002-deed-11e5-8d98-4b3d9215ade1_story.html |title = San Antonio Missions preserve Native American history in Texas’s first World Heritage Site |last = Barnett |first = Tracy L. |date = 2016-03-10 |publisher = The Washington Post |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-05 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210130232420if_/https://www.washingtonpost.com/lifestyle/travel/san-antonio-missions-preserve-native-american-history-at-the-nations-newest-world-heritage-site/2016/03/10/69356002-deed-11e5-8d98-4b3d9215ade1_story.html |archivedate = 2021-01-30}}</ref><ref name="Hester@1975">{{Cite journal |last = Hester |first = Thomas R. |url = https://scholarworks.sfasu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1597&context=ita |title = Archaeological and Historical Resources in the San Antonio-Guadalupe River Basins: A Preliminary Statement Guadalupe River Basins: A Preliminary Statement |journal = Index of Texas Archaeology: Open Access Gray Literature from the Lone Star State |year = 1975 |volume = 1975 |access-date = 2021-02-12 |archive-date = 2021-03-04 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20210304145225/https://scholarworks.sfasu.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1597&context=ita |dead-url = no }}</ref>。這些原住民主要以{{tsl|en|Coahuiltecan|柯庫兒太肯}}為主，他們多以[[狩獵採集|狩獵採集]]為生，並會在冬季遷徙至海岸一帶並在夏季返回內陸地區{{sfn|Newcomb, Jr.|1961|pp=54-55}}{{sfn|Raycraft|Beckett|2006|p=7}}<ref name="Hester@1975"/><ref name="NativeAmerican@1500-1700">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sanantonio.gov/Mission-Trails/Prehistory-History/History-of-San-Antonio/Native-American-Occupation |title = Native American Occupation (1500-1700) |author = City of San Antonio |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-05 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201111012552/https://www.sanantonio.gov/Mission-Trails/Prehistory-History/History-of-San-Antonio/Native-American-Occupation |archivedate = 2020-11-11}}</ref>。河流源頭的聖安東尼奧泉以及附近的聖佩德羅溫泉對當地美洲原住民來說十分神聖，他們認為水泉是通往冥府的門戶，而聖安東尼奧河則是生命之源<ref name="HistoryOfSAR_SAM0920">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sanantoniomag.com/the-history-behind-the-san-antonio-river/ |title = The History Behind the San Antonio River |last = Winesett |first = Claire |date = 2020-09 |publisher = San Antonio Magazine |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-06 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200927060803/https://www.sanantoniomag.com/the-history-behind-the-san-antonio-river/ |archivedate = 2020-09-27}}</ref>。1500年代未，歐洲人開始零星地進入德克薩斯南部及中部地區<ref name="NativeAmerican@1500-1700"/>。1535年，西班牙探險家[[阿爾瓦·努涅斯·卡韋薩·德·巴卡|阿爾瓦·努涅斯·卡韋薩·德·巴卡]]在他穿越德克薩斯的旅程中曾經經過河流<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv"/>。但是，有些歷史學家認為阿爾瓦·努涅斯·卡韋薩·德·巴卡早在1520年代便早已發現河流，並在其上游紮營<ref name="Noonan-Guerra@1987">{{Cite web |url = https://www.uiw.edu/sanantonio/IndiansofSanAntonioRiver.html |title = Indians of the San Antonio River: Yanaguana - Journal of San Antonio |last = Noonan-Guerra |first = Mary Ann |year = 1987 |publisher = University of the Incarnate Word |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-05 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201126041144/https://www.uiw.edu/sanantonio/IndiansofSanAntonioRiver.html |archivedate = 2020-11-26}}</ref>。在1600年代後期，一些能夠接觸到歐洲馬匹的原住民部落開始遷移至德薩斯南部平原，包括{{tsl|en|Lipan Apache people|阿帕契族立邦部落}}、{{tsl|en|Tonkawa|通卡瓦人}}及[[科曼奇人|科曼奇人]]<ref name="NativeAmerican@1500-1700"/>。1689年，西班牙探險家{{tsl|en|Alonso de León|阿隆索·德·利昂}}在他第四次前往德克薩斯的探險中把河流稱為「阿羅約德利昂」（{{lang|es|Arroyo de León}}）{{sfn|Buck|1980|p=67}}{{sfn|Foster|Baumgartner|1992|p=19}}。河流現時的名稱則是源於1691年，當時[[新西班牙總督轄區|新西班牙]]德克薩斯州州長{{tsl|en|Domingo Terán de los Ríos|多明哥·泰蘭·德洛斯里奧斯}}正與西班牙神父{{tsl|en|Damián Massanet|達米安·馬薩涅}}一同巡視德克薩斯東部的傳教站，適逢當日是天主教紀念日[[羅馬天主教聖人曆|聖安多尼瞻禮日]]，於是德洛斯里奧斯在經過河流時把它命名為聖安東尼奧<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv"/>{{sfn|Buck|1980|p=67}}{{sfn|Foster|Baumgartner|1992|p=13}}。同時，他們在河流附近發現一條名為「{{tsl|en|Yanaguana (San Antonio)|亞南瓜納}}」的原住民村莊（遺址位於現今的聖安東尼奧市），其後馬薩涅神父把村莊更名為「聖安東尼奧·德·帕多瓦」（{{lang|es|San Antonio de Padua}}），並為當地居民及西班牙士兵提供彌撒<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv"/>。1692年，西班牙人在河源附近建造了首個永久聚落{{sfn|Corner|1890|p=51}}。

=== 18至19世紀 ===
[[File:FrayAntoniotexas.JPG|thumb]]
自1690年開始，德克薩斯便成為[[新西班牙總督轄區|新西班牙]]的省份，而河源至河口一帶亦由西班牙人控制{{sfn|Corner|1890|p=51}}。1709年，西班牙[[傳教士|傳教士]]{{tsl|en|Antonio de Olivares|安東尼奧·德·奧利瓦雷斯}}參與由探險家{{tsl|en|Pedro de Aguirre|佩德羅·德·阿吉雷}}率領的探險隊，探索德克薩斯中南部地區，範圍由現今的聖安東尼奧市至[[科羅拉多河_(德克薩斯州)|科羅拉多河]]{{sfn|Foster|Baumgartner|1992|p=55}}。奧利瓦雷斯發現聖安東尼奧一帶有著豐富的水資源，是在這片半乾旱地區建立傳教站的理想之地。為了擴大德克薩斯地區的傳教活動，他之後返回西班牙並遊說當局在聖安東尼奧河岸上建立傳教站<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/olivares-antonio-de-san-buenaventura-y |title = Olivares, Antonio de San Buenaventura y (ca. 1600–ca. 1700) |last = Chipman |first = Donald E. |publisher = Texas State Historical Association |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-06 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201102014615/https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/olivares-antonio-de-san-buenaventura-y |archivedate = 2020-11-02}}</ref>。1718年5月1日，奧利瓦雷斯在獲得新西班牙總督{{tsl|en|Baltasar de Zúñiga, 1st Duke of Arión|祖尼加的巴爾塔沙，第一代阿里昂公爵}}的正式批准後，帶領其他[[方濟各會|方濟各會]]傳教士建立了[[阿拉莫_(得克萨斯州)|聖安東尼奧·德·瓦萊羅傳教站]]{{sfn|Corner|1890|p=69}}{{sfn|Chipman|1992|p=117}}<ref name="Mission San Antonio de Valero@NPS">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nps.gov/subjects/travelspanishmissions/mission-san-antonio-de-valero-the-alamo.htm |title = Mission San Antonio de Valero, The Alamo -- Spanish Colonial Missions of the Southwest Travel Itinerary |author = National Park Service |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-06 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210203012939/https://www.nps.gov/subjects/travelspanishmissions/mission-san-antonio-de-valero-the-alamo.htm |archivedate = 2021-02-03}}</ref>。數日後，[[西屬德克薩斯|西屬德克薩斯]]州長{{tsl|en|Martín de Alarcón|馬丁·德·阿拉爾孔}}在傳教站對面，即河流西岸建立了{{tsl|en|Presidio San Antonio de Béxar|聖安東尼奧·德·貝克薩要塞}}<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv"/>{{sfn|Chipman|1992|p=117}}。充足的飲用水、灌溉用水及水力資源使河流迅速成為西班牙在德克薩斯的傳教活動中心，並促使當地政府在1720年至1755年間先後興建額外四個傳教站，分別是{{tsl|en|Mission San José (Texas)|聖何塞傳教站 (德克薩斯州)|聖何塞傳教站}}、{{tsl|en|Mission San Juan Capistrano (Texas)|聖胡安·卡皮斯特拉諾傳教站 (德克薩斯州)|聖胡安·卡皮斯特拉諾傳教站}}、{{tsl|en|Mission San Francisco de la Espada|劍之聖弗朗西斯科傳教站}}以及{{tsl|en|Mission Concepcion|康塞普西翁傳教站}}{{sfn|Corner|1890|pp=14, 17, 20-21}}。另外在1749年，數個位於瓜達盧佩河的傳教站遷移至河流下游，後來成為[[戈利亞德_(得克萨斯州)|戈利亞德]]<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv"/>{{sfn|Chipman|1992|p=171}}。1776年，當地政府打算在河流下游一帶興建溝渠，一度引發水權爭議<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987">{{Cite web |url = https://www.uiw.edu/sanantonio/sevenacequias.html |title = The San Antonio River and its Seven Acequias - Journal of San Antonio |last = Noonan-Guerra |first = Mary Ann |year = 1987 |publisher = University of the Incarnate Word |language = en |accessdate = 2021-01-02 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190601231615/https://www.uiw.edu/sanantonio/sevenacequias.html |archivedate = 2019-09-27}}</ref>。下游的傳教站向當局要求獲得這些灌溉用水的優先使用權，但來自[[加那利亞群島|加那利亞群島]]的殖民者鄰居則拿出皇家法令，指「傳教站不能在供水未被中斷的情況下阻止他人自由使用河水作灌溉之用」，最終傳教站負責人只好作罷<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>。方濟各會的傳教活動一直持續到18世紀末，但後來因疾病及搶劫等因素對居於聚落的原住民造成重大損失，加上他們普遍不願接受西班牙的生活方式，最終這些傳教站在1793年開始[[世俗化|世俗化]]，並轉變為自治的原住民村落<ref name="Mission San Antonio de Valero@NPS"/>{{sfn|Chipman|1992|p=204}}。

[[File:1854_Alamo.jpg|thumb]]
1810年，[[墨西哥獨立戰爭|墨西哥獨立戰爭]]爆發。1821年，[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]擺脫西班牙統治並成功獨立。1824年4月，在墨西哥政府頒佈較西班牙統治時期嚴格的《{{tsl|en|General Colonization Law|一般殖民法}}》前，墨西哥人{{tsl|en|Martín De León|馬丁·德·利昂}}向[[墨屬德克薩斯|墨屬德克薩斯]]聖安東尼奧·德·貝克薩爾省代表團提出請願，要求在河流下游一帶建立城鎮來安置40多個墨西哥家庭，並獲得批准<ref name="De Leon's Colony">{{Cite web |url = https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/de-leons-colony |title = De Leon's Colony |last = Roell |first = Craig H. |publisher = Texas State Historical Association |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201026022114/https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/de-leons-colony |archivedate = 2020-10-26}}</ref>。1820年代後期，在[[科阿韋拉及德克薩斯|科阿韋拉及德克薩斯]]頒佈《殖民法》後，屬於[[Empresario|Empresario]]的{{tsl|en|James Power (empresario)|詹姆斯·鮑爾}}及{{tsl|en|James Hewetson|詹姆斯·希森}}兩人共同向當局提出申請，與一些愛爾蘭天主教徒及墨西哥家庭殖民德克薩斯海岸<ref name="Power and Hewetson Colony">{{Cite web |url = https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/power-and-hewetson-colony |title = Power and Hewetson Colony |publisher = Texas State Historical Association |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210203030137/https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/power-and-hewetson-colony |archivedate = 2021-02-03}}</ref>。及後，他們獲分配至一個鄰近河流且已被遺棄的傳教站，並建立殖民地<ref name="Power and Hewetson Colony"/>。1835年10月，隨著[[冈萨雷斯之战|冈萨雷斯之战]]爆發，[[德克薩斯革命|德克薩斯革命]]正式開始。在革命期間，多場戰役先後在河流一帶爆發，包括{{tsl|en|Battle of Concepción|康塞普西翁之戰}}、[[草料戰鬥|草料戰鬥]]、{{tsl|en|Siege of Béxar|圍攻貝克薩}}、{{tsl|en|Goliad massacre|戈利亞德大屠殺}}及[[阿拉摩之戰|阿拉摩之戰]]<ref name="TSHA_SanAntonioRv"/>。阿拉摩要塞前身是聖安東尼奧·德·瓦萊羅傳教站，在1793年因西班牙世俗化運動而被廢棄，後來一支西班牙騎兵部隊進駐此地並建立營地，又把它更名為「阿拉摩」{{sfn|Chipman|1992|p=202}}<ref name="Battle of Alamo">{{Cite web |url = https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/alamo-battle-of-the |title = Battle of the Alamo |last = Hardin |first = Stephen L. |publisher = Texas State Historical Association |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210118205849/https://www.tshaonline.org/handbook/entries/alamo-battle-of-the |archivedate = 2021-01-18}}</ref>。1836年2月下旬，墨西哥將軍和獨裁者[[安東尼奧·羅培茲·德·聖塔·安那|安東尼奧·羅培茲·德·聖塔·安那]]率軍1,800人，把[[德克萨斯共和国|德克萨斯共和国]]數以百計的士兵圍困在阿拉摩要塞<ref name="Battle of Alamo"/>。經過13天圍困後，墨西哥一方突襲要塞，造成幾乎所有德克薩斯士兵死亡，阿拉摩之戰宣告結束<ref name="Battle of Alamo"/>。在1861至1865年的[[南北戰爭|南北戰爭]]中，具有地理位置優勢的聖安東尼奧市一度成為[[美利堅聯盟國|美利堅聯盟國]]的補給站<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.expressnews.com/news/local/article/San-Antonio-s-complicated-history-as-a-11095099.php |title = San Antonio’s complicated history as a Confederate supply depot |last = Lawrence |first = J.P. |date = 2017-04-26 |publisher = San Antonio Express-News |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811103413/https://www.expressnews.com/news/local/article/San-Antonio-s-complicated-history-as-a-11095099.php |archivedate = 2020-08-11}}</ref>。1877年，聖安東尼奧市向當地一家公司批出供水合同，而後者則在河源附近建設泵房抽取並向該市供水{{sfn|Corner|1890|pp=54-55}}。同年，{{tsl|en|Buffalo Bayou, Brazos and Colorado Railway|加爾維斯頓、哈里斯堡與聖安東尼奧鐵路公司}}把旗下鐵路延伸至河流上游一帶，並為聖安東尼奧市帶來商業及人口增長<ref name="Railroad">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sanantonio.gov/Mission-Trails/Prehistory-History/History-of-San-Antonio/Railroad-Era-and-Industrial-Development/Railroad-Era-and-Industrial-Development-Narrative |title = The Railroad Era and Industrial Development |publisher = City of San Antonio |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201021075506/https://www.sanantonio.gov/Mission-Trails/Prehistory-History/History-of-San-Antonio/Railroad-Era-and-Industrial-Development/Railroad-Era-and-Industrial-Development-Narrative |archivedate = 2020-10-21}}</ref>。數年後，{{tsl|en|International–Great Northern Railroad|國際—大北方鐵路公司}}亦連接至聖安東尼奧市，使該市逐漸成為區域性的商業、農業加工和運輸中心<ref name="Railroad"/>。1890年，聖安東尼奧市的水力公司開始使用[[自流含水層|自流井]]從愛德華茲含水層取水，使該市對水的依賴由河流轉為水井，及後更影響鄰近水泉及河流的流量<ref name="HistoryOfSAR_SAM0920"/>。

=== 20世紀至今 ===
[[File:1998_South_Central_Texas_Flood_1.png|thumb]]
1913年，[[厄爾尼諾現象|厄爾尼諾現象]]出現，而此時德克薩斯州降雨十分充沛<ref name="Salinas@mysa_150306">{{Cite web |url = https://www.mysanantonio.com/150years/major-stories/slideshow/Major-floods-of-Texas-104824.php |title = Major floods of Texas |last = Salinas |first = Rebecca |date = 2015-03-06 |publisher = mysanantonio.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201029084729/https://www.mysanantonio.com/150years/major-stories/slideshow/Major-floods-of-Texas-104824.php |archivedate = 2020-10-29}}</ref>。同年10月及12月，河流鄰近聖安東尼奧市一帶先後發生兩次洪災，其中10月那次更在24小時內錄得超過180毫米（7英寸）雨量，而這兩次洪災合共造成五人死亡、約30萬美元的經濟損失<ref name="Milestones">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/about/history/san-antonio-river-milestones |title = San Antonio River Milestones |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-07 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210201155814/https://www.sariverauthority.org/about/history/san-antonio-river-milestones |archivedate = 2021-02-01}}</ref>。1921年9月，洪水再次掩至聖安東尼奧市，市內錄得173毫米（6.83英寸）雨量，而鄰近地區則在36小時內合共錄得1,010毫米（39.7英寸）雨量，河流水位亦一度上升至3.7米（12英尺）並淹浸多棟市中心建築物<ref name="Salinas@mysa_150306"/><ref name="1998Flood">{{Cite web |url = https://www.weather.gov/ewx/wxevent-1998flood |title = South Central Texas Flood Event - October 1998 |author = National Weather Service |publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201017124457/https://www.weather.gov/ewx/wxevent-1998flood |archivedate = 2020-10-17}}</ref><ref name="WeatherEvents_1900s">{{Cite web |url = https://www.weather.gov/media/ewx/wxevents/ewx-1900s.pdf |title = 10 MOST SIGNIFICANT WEATHER EVENTS OF THE 1900S FOR AUSTIN, DEL RIO AND SAN ANTONIO AND VICINITY |author = National Weather Service |date = 1999-12-28 |publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201017124525/https://www.weather.gov/media/ewx/wxevents/ewx-1900s.pdf |archivedate = 2020-10-17}}</ref>。最終，這場破壞性極大的洪災奪去51條生命，造成大量房屋、基建及公共建築受損，並帶來超過3百萬美元的經濟損失<ref name="HistoryOfSAR_SAM0920"/><ref name="Milestones"/><ref name="Allen@SAEN_150523">{{Cite web |url = https://www.expressnews.com/life/life_columnists/paula_allen/article/Scenic-dam-drive-scrapped-for-security-6283402.php |title = Scenic dam drive scrapped for security |last = Allen |first = Paula |date = 2015-05-23 |publisher = San Antonio Express-News |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-09 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200920042728/https://www.expressnews.com/life/life_columnists/paula_allen/article/Scenic-dam-drive-scrapped-for-security-6283402.php |archivedate = 2020-09-20}}</ref>。災難過後，市長約翰·托賓（{{lang|en|John Tobin}}）提出在奧爾莫斯盆地修建水壩、橋樑及下水道等設施，以防同類事件再次出現，同時亦刺激河流的現代發展<ref name="HistoryOfSAR_SAM0920"/>。其後該市發行城市債券，用以修建市區水道及奧爾莫斯水壩<ref name="Allen@SAEN_150523"/>。在聖安東尼奧商會的幫助下，該市債券發行規模達到約280萬美元，及後市政府分配約60萬美元興建市區水道，而餘下款項則全數用於修建水壩<ref name="Allen@SAEN_150523"/>。1937年，聖安東尼奧河管理局正式成立，旨在協助當地的防洪工作<ref name="HistoryOfSAR_SAM0920"/>。1941年，當地建築師{{tsl|en|Robert H.H. Hugman|羅伯特·H·H·哈格曼}}所提倡的城市公園{{tsl|en|San Antonio River Walk|聖安東尼奧河濱步道}}幾經努力後終於落成，並在後來的{{tsl|en|HemisFair '68|1968年聖安東尼奧世界博覽會}}為眾多遊客提供服務<ref name="HistoryOfSAR_SAM0920"/>。1946年洪災過後，聖安東尼奧河管理局與[[美國陸軍工兵部隊|美國陸軍工兵部隊]]及[[美國農業部|美國農業部]]{{tsl|en|Natural Resources Conservation Service|自然資源保護局}}合作，著手制定聖安東尼奧河及其支流的洪水管理戰略<ref name="SACIP@SARA">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/about/history/san-antonio-channel-improvement-project-sacip |title = San Antonio Channel Improvement Project (SACIP) |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-10 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201129015919/https://www.sariverauthority.org/about/history/san-antonio-channel-improvement-project-sacip |archivedate = 2020-11-29}}</ref>。而在1998年10月中旬，兩股颶風（[[1998年颶風萊斯特|颶風萊斯特]]及[[1998年颶風瑪德琳|颶風瑪德琳]]）配合其他氣象條件，在德克薩斯州中南部地區形成暴雨，最終誘發洪災<ref name="USGS1999">{{Cite web |url = https://pubs.usgs.gov/fs/FS-147-99/pdf/fs-147-99.pdf |title = Floods in the Guadalupe and San Antonio RiverBasins in Texas, October 1998 |author = U.S. Geological Survey |year = 1999 |publisher = U.S. Department of the Interior |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200817051339/https://pubs.usgs.gov/fs/FS-147-99/pdf/fs-147-99.pdf |archivedate = 2020-08-17}}</ref>。當時，聖安東尼奧市內錄得約286毫米（11.26英寸）雨量，打破1921年的記錄，而鄰近[[410號州際公路|410號州際公路]]的河段其水位高度亦稍微超出正常水位，但流量則錄得破記錄的2,250立方米每秒（79,400立方英尺每秒）<ref name="1998Flood"/><ref name="WeatherEvents_1900s"/><ref name="USGS1999"/>。事件最終造成25人死亡，並帶來超過500萬美元的經濟損失<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.mysanantonio.com/news/local/history-culture/article/Record-setting-flood-of-1998-that-killed-25-9984276.php |title = Record-setting flood of 1998 that killed 25 happened 19 years ago this week |last = White |first = Tyler |date = 2016-10-19 |publisher = mysanantonio.com |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180211052402/https://www.mysanantonio.com/news/local/history-culture/article/Record-setting-flood-of-1998-that-killed-25-9984276.php |archivedate = 2018-02-11}}</ref>。

2002年6月下旬，受高空擾動影響，德克薩斯州中南部地區出現暴雨，更一度錄得760毫米（30英寸）的降雨量<ref name="2002Flood">{{Cite web |url = https://www.weather.gov/crp/20020717_Flood |title = Disastrous River Flooding - June 30 Through July 17, 2002 |author = National Weather Service |publisher = National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201017055942/https://www.weather.gov/crp/20020717_Flood |archivedate = 2020-10-17}}</ref>。暴雨在聖安東尼奧地區及德克薩斯州丘陵地區一帶引發氾濫，最終河流上游出現洪災，並造成數人死亡及數千萬美元的經濟損失<ref name="2002Flood"/><ref name="nytimes@020706">{{Cite web |url = https://www.nytimes.com/2002/07/06/us/more-rain-worsens-flooding-in-areas-around-san-antonio.html |title = More Rain Worsens Flooding in Areas Around San Antonio |author = The Associated Press |date = 2002-07-06 |publisher = The New York Times |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150527203401/http://www.nytimes.com/2002/07/06/us/more-rain-worsens-flooding-in-areas-around-san-antonio.html |archivedate = 2015-05-27}}</ref>。經歷1998年及2002年兩次洪災後，比爾縣專員法院（{{lang|en|Bexar County Commissioners Court}}）、聖安東尼奧市議會及聖安東尼奧河管理局董事會在2003年達成協議，建立比爾區域流域管理夥伴關係（{{lang|en|Bexar Regional Watershed Management Partners}}），旨在利用專業技術及整合資源來改善水質、防洪及雨水管理<ref name="Milestones"/><ref name="BRWM">{{Cite web |url = https://www.bexar.org/2661/Bexar-Regional-Watershed-Management-Part |title = Bexar Regional Watershed Management Partners |author = Bexar County Courthouse |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201017000556/https://www.bexar.org/2661/Bexar-Regional-Watershed-Management-Part |archivedate = 2020-10-17}}</ref>。2012年，聖安東尼奧河管理局聯同{{tsl|en|Kenedy, Texas|凱內迪 (德克薩斯州)|凱內迪}}市政府保育位於市內的河流支流埃斯孔迪多溪（{{lang|en|Escondido Creek}}），並在往後數年成功把溪流延長2.01公里（1.25英里），以及增建公園大道及休閒設施<ref name="Milestones"/><ref name="2020HighlightReport">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/sites/default/files/2020-06/fy2020_sar_character_report-web.pdf |title = 2020 Clean Rivers Program - San Antonio River Basin Highlight Report |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210208083115/https://www.sariverauthority.org/sites/default/files/2020-06/fy2020_sar_character_report-web.pdf |archivedate = 2021-02-08}}</ref>。隨著聖安東尼奧市及毗連區域的人口逐步增長，市內用水量亦逐漸提高，單在2018年1月至7月便已超過1,700億公升（460億加侖），河流流量亦因而有所下降<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://www.expressnews.com/news/local/article/San-Antonio-residents-companies-water-use-13159113.php |title = Some San Antonio residents have used more than 1M gallons of water so far this year. Here's why |last = Chavey |first = S. M. |date = 2018-08-15 |publisher = San Antonio Express-News |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20191230110246if_/https://www.expressnews.com/news/local/article/San-Antonio-residents-companies-water-use-13159113.php#photo-16021606 |archivedate = 2019-12-30}}</ref><ref name="Zhao, Gao & Cuo@2016">{{cite conference |last1 = Zhao |first1 = Gang |last2 = Gao |first2 = Huilin |last3 = Cuo |first3 = Lan |title = Effects of Urbanization and Climate Change on Peak Flows over the San Antonio River Basin, Texas |journal = Journal of Hydrometeorology |year = 2016 |volume = 17 |issue = 9 |pages= 2371-2389}}</ref>。

== 河流改造 ==
早在18世紀，居於當地的傳教士及印第安人已建造不同的水渠來引導河水用於灌溉<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>{{sfn|Corner|1890|pp=41-43}}。但是，流域內主要的水渠是由後來的定居者所建造<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>{{sfn|Corner|1890|pp=41-43}}。在1729年至1745年之間，當地政府先後興建六條水渠，包括康塞普西翁溝渠（{{lang|en|Conception Ditch}}）、阿拉莫馬德雷溝渠（{{lang|en|Alamo Madre Ditch}}）、聖何塞灌溉水渠（{{lang|en|San Jose Acequia}}）、聖胡安灌溉水渠（{{lang|en|San Juan Acequia}}）及聖佩德羅溝渠（{{lang|en|San Pedro Ditch}}），而部份更鄰近各個市內傳教站<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>{{sfn|Corner|1890|pp=43-45}}。這些水渠主要向傳教站及附近農田供水，只有聖佩德羅溝渠是負責向區內另一個城鎮「聖費爾南多別墅」（{{lang|es|Villa de San Fernando}}）供水<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>{{sfn|Corner|1890|p=44}}。19世紀中後期，這些水渠因不同原因而被棄用，時至今日只有阿拉莫馬德雷溝渠及聖胡安灌溉水渠仍然正常運作，而後者亦負責為聖安東尼奧南部數個農場供水<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>。埃斯帕達水壩是當地政府在聖安東尼奧·德·瓦萊羅傳教站南部進行的最後一項水利工程，它除了水壩外亦附有溝渠及[[渡槽|渡槽]]等建造物<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>。項目在1731年開始，1745年完工，是美國現存最古老的水壩<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/>。埃斯帕達溝渠本在1880年代停止使用，但在1895年埃斯帕達溝渠公司（{{lang|en|Espada Ditch Company}}）清理、拓寬及加深溝渠，並修復埃斯帕達水壩，再次向周遭農民供水<ref name="Acequias@Noonan-Guerra_1987"/><ref>{{Cite web |url = https://digitalrepository.unm.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1031&context=shri_publications |title = Restoring The Oldest Water Right In Texas: LandGrant Suertes, Water Dulas, and Archimedes ScrewPumps |last = Rivera |first = Jose A. |date = 2009-06-01 |publisher = The University of New Mexico |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-08 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200709052116/https://digitalrepository.unm.edu/cgi/viewcontent.cgi?article=1031&context=shri_publications |archivedate = 2020-07-09}}</ref>。

1921年9月發生的洪災極具破壞性，促使時任市長約翰·托賓提出修建防洪設施以防同類事件再次發生，而奧爾莫斯水壩亦因此應運而生<ref name="HistoryOfSAR_SAM0920"/>。在進行一系列的地質、大氣條件及降水歷史研究後，市政府決定從阿拉莫高地開發商及{{tsl|en|Sisters of Charity of the Incarnate Word|聖道慈惠姊妹會}}手上收購土地，並預定在阿拉莫高地西南部興建水壩<ref name="Allen@SAEN_150523"/>。這座耗資150萬美元的水壩於1925年開始建設，並在1926年完成<ref name="OlmosDam@TWDB">{{Cite web |url = https://www.twdb.texas.gov/surfacewater/rivers/reservoirs/olmos/index.asp |title = Olmos Reservoir (San Antonio River Basin) |author = Texas Water Development Board |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-09 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201016173512/https://www.twdb.texas.gov/surfacewater/rivers/reservoirs/olmos/index.asp |archivedate = 2020-10-16}}</ref><ref name="Witcher@CEM_Apr16">{{cite magazine |url = https://ascelibrary.org/doi/pdf/10.1061/ciegag.0001093 |title = History Lesson: San Antonio's River Walk |last = Witcher |first = T.R. |date = April 2016 |magazine = Civil Engineering Magazine |publisher = The South African Institution of Civil Engineering |volume = 86 |issue = 4 |pages = 46-49 |ISSN = 2381-0688 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-09 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210209144347/https://ascelibrary.org/doi/pdf/10.1061/ciegag.0001093 |archivedate = 2021-02-09}}</ref><ref name="OlmosDam@SARA">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/services/flood-management/engineering-projects/olmos-dam |title = Olmos Dam |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-10 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201025155526/https://www.sariverauthority.org/services/flood-management/engineering-projects/olmos-dam |archivedate = 2020-10-25}}</ref>。水壩屬於[[重力壩|混凝土重力壩]]，長592米（1,941英尺），高18米（60英尺）<ref name="OlmosDam@TWDB"/><ref name="OlmosDamSpec">{{Cite web |url = http://www.twdb.texas.gov/surfacewater/rivers/reservoirs/plates/san_antonio/existing/olmos.pdf |title = Olmos Dam and Olmos Reservoir |author = City of San Antonio |publisher = Texas Water Development Board |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-09 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200907130403/https://www.twdb.texas.gov/surfacewater/rivers/reservoirs/plates/san_antonio/existing/olmos.pdf |archivedate = 2020-09-07}}</ref>。另外，水庫面積為83平方公里（32平方英里），最大蓄水量約為15,500,000立方米（12,600英畝·英尺）<ref name="OlmosDam@TWDB"/><ref name="OlmosDamSpec"/>。水壩透過六個水閘控制及阻擋水流，並可在洪水發生時逐漸把水注入河道，確保水不會溢出河道<ref name="Allen@SAEN_150523"/><ref name="Witcher@CEM_Apr16"/>。在暴風雨侵襲期間，水壩合共阻止約190億公升（51億加侖）的水溢出河道造成市區氾濫<ref name="Witcher@CEM_Apr16"/>。1970年代初，市政府委託民間工程公司來調查水壩的結構完整性、穩定性及承載能力<ref name="OlmosDam@SARA"/>。調查結果指出水壩能阻擋二百年一遇洪水，但存在穩定性及侵蝕問題，因此建議市政府加固水壩結構<ref name="OlmosDam@SARA"/>{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|p=9}}。1979年，水壩改造計劃正式展開，項目包括加固及錨定大壩、修改水閘操作、增設緊急溢洪道等，後來亦在鄰近街道的水壩控制中心安裝監控儀器<ref name="OlmosDam@SARA"/>。

1926年，建築師{{tsl|en|Robert H.H. Hugman|羅伯特·H·H·哈格曼}}向市政府、業主及民間領袖推銷其城市規劃方案，包括修建防洪水閘、小型水壩、扇形閘門以及進行河道截斷工程等<ref name="flood-risk">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/flood-risk |title = Flood Risk |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-09 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201021072017/https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/flood-risk |archivedate = 2020-10-21}}</ref>。但是，大多建築計劃因[[經濟大蕭條|經濟大蕭條]]而遭擱置，只有河道截斷工程在1926年展開，並在1930年完成<ref name="flood-risk"/>。1954年，美國國會授權[[美國陸軍工程兵團|美國陸軍工程兵團]]進行聖安東尼奧河道改善項目，以提升聖安東尼奧河及其支流的防洪能力<ref name="SACIP@SARA"/>{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|pp=5-7}}。1958年，工程兵團與聖安東尼奧河管理局合作，改建長約50公里（31英里）的河道並把其渠道化，又在河流及聖佩德羅溪下方興建兩條地下隧道，以保護政府大樓及商業區免受洪水威脅<ref name="SACIP@SARA"/>{{sfn|U.S. Army Corps of Engineers|1972|pp=5-7}}。大多防洪工程分別在1960年代和1970年代完成，但兩條地下隧道的施工時間則較後<ref name="Witcher@CEM_Apr16"/>。工程兵團在1993年展開聖安東尼奧河隧道的修建工作，並於1998年完成<ref name="SARA@201006">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/whats-new/blog/san-antonio-river-tunnel-protecting-downtown-san-antonio |title = San Antonio River Tunnel - Protecting Downtown San Antonio |author = San Antonio River Authority |date = 2020-10-06 |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-10 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201020003730/https://www.sariverauthority.org/whats-new/blog/san-antonio-river-tunnel-protecting-downtown-san-antonio |archivedate = 2020-10-20}}</ref><ref name="RegionalFloodMitigationPlan2000">{{Cite web |url = https://www.twdb.texas.gov/publications/reports/contracted_reports/doc/2000001011.pdf |title = City of San Antonio Regional Flood Mitigation Plan |author = Pape-Dawson Engineers, Inc. |year = 2000 |publisher = Texas Water Development Board |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-10 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201017113109/http://www.twdb.texas.gov/publications/reports/contracted_reports/doc/2000001011.pdf |archivedate = 2020-10-17}}</ref>。這條造價約1.11億美元的隧道深46米（150英尺），長約4.8公里（3英里），直徑達7.3米（24英尺），在洪災期間能每分鐘排走約1,200萬公升（300萬加侖）的水<ref name="SARA@201006"/><ref name="RegionalFloodMitigationPlan2000"/>。除了防洪，隧道亦能在乾旱時期把河水循環到河流中以維持一定流量<ref name="SARA@201006"/>。1999年，隧道項目獲得美國土木工程師學會的德克薩斯州傑出土木工程成就獎，以及國家級優異獎<ref name="SARA@201006"/>。2000年，該項目獲美國國家藝術基金會頒發聯邦設計成就獎<ref name="SARA@201006"/>。

== 休閒 ==
[[File:Sanantonio_alamo.jpg|thumb]]
聖安東尼奧河流域內設有多個公園及步道供公眾使用。前身是傳教站的[[阿拉莫_(得克萨斯州)|阿拉摩要塞]]在1836年[[阿拉摩之戰|阿拉摩之戰]]期間受損，但直到1890年代後期才有組織嘗試修復及保育。1960年12月19日，阿拉摩要塞獲聯邦政府收錄至[[美國國家歷史名勝|美國國家歷史名勝]]<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://npgallery.nps.gov/NRHP/GetAsset/NHLS/66000808_text |title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory-Nomination:the Spanish Governor's Palace |last = Heintzelman |first = Patricia |year = 1975 |publisher = National Park Service |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-10 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210210125048/https://npgallery.nps.gov/NRHP/GetAsset/NHLS/66000808_text |archivedate = 2021-02-10}}</ref>。除了參與導賞團及歷史講座外，公眾還可以在阿拉摩內參觀小教堂、長軍營及小型博物館，而博物館內則收藏著德克薩斯革命時期的繪畫、武器及其他文物{{sfn|Thompson|2001|p=121}}。另外，阿拉摩設有一幅名為「歷史牆」的大型壁畫，描繪阿拉莫建築群從傳教站時期至現代的歷史{{sfn|Thompson|2001|p=119}}。1983年4月，{{tsl|en|San Antonio Missions National Historical Park|聖安東尼奧傳教站國家歷史公園}}成立，範圍包括四個在西班牙殖民時期興建的傳教站，以及相關的水壩和灌溉水渠，但由於阿拉摩是由德州擁有，因此被排除在外<ref name="SAMNHP">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sanantonio.gov/Mission-Trails/Mission-Trails-Historic-Sites/Detail-Page/ArtMID/16185/ArticleID/4453/San-Antonio-Missions-National-Historical-Park |title = San Antonio Missions National Historical Park |author = City of San Antonio |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-10 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210210134104/https://www.sanantonio.gov/Mission-Trails/Mission-Trails-Historic-Sites/Detail-Page/ArtMID/16185/ArticleID/4453/San-Antonio-Missions-National-Historical-Park |archivedate = 2021-02-10}}</ref>。公眾除了能免費遊覽園內各個殖民時期遺址外，亦可以在劍之聖弗朗西斯科傳教站觀看原住民傳統手藝「[[梭織|梭織]]」表演<ref name="SAMNHP"/>。2015年，[[聯合國教科文組織|聯合國教科文組織]]把五個傳教站及相關建築列入[[世界遺產|世界遺產]]<ref>{{Cite web |url = https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1466/ |title = San Antonio Missions |author = UNESCO World Heritage Centre |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-10 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210124130727/https://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1466/ |archivedate = 2021-01-24}}</ref>。

[[File:Casa_Rio_in_San_Antonio.jpg|thumb]]
{{tsl|en|San Antonio River Walk|聖安東尼奧河濱步道}}是聖安東尼奧市內的城市公園，同時亦是河道美化工程的一部份<ref name="SARW_OurHistory">{{Cite web |url = https://www.thesanantonioriverwalk.com/about/our-history/ |title = San Antonio River Walk - Our History |author = The River Walk |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201230074638/https://www.thesanantonioriverwalk.com/about/our-history/ |archivedate = 2020-12-30}}</ref><ref name="Alcalde@MayJun2003">{{cite magazine |last = Speck |first = Larry |title = The Odd Couple |magazine = The Alcalde |date = May/June 2003 |volume = 91 |issue = 5 |page = 80 |location = Austin, TX |publisher = Emmis Communications |ISSN = 1535-993X |language = en}}</ref>。長約5.2公里（17,000英尺）的河濱步道建於1941年，它一共覆蓋21個街區，沿途設有多條樓梯及橋樑，並種植超過12,000棵植物<ref name="Alcalde@MayJun2003"/>。在接下來的幾十年中，市政府不斷改善及擴展河濱步道，使它連接至商業區、會議中心及劇院等地<ref name="SARW_OurHistory"/><ref name="SARW_OurHistory"/>。現時的河濱步道由博物館段、市中心段及傳教站段組成，長約26公里（16英里），公眾可以透過它前往市中心及市內著名景點（如珍珠釀酒廠、藝術博物館等），而步道兩旁食肆商店林立<ref name="SARW_OurHistory"/><ref name="mission-reach">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/parks-trails/san-antonio-river-walk-mission-reach |title = San Antonio River Walk Mission Reach |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-11 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201225084102/https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/parks-trails/san-antonio-river-walk-mission-reach |archivedate = 2020-12-25}}</ref>。另外，公眾亦可在某些段落乘坐駁船遊覽，甚或進行遠足、騎單車、劃獨木舟及皮划艇等活動<ref name="Alcalde@MayJun2003"/><ref name="mission-reach"/>。

除了上述位靠聖安東尼奧市的公園及河濱步道外，河流流域內還有不少休閒設施。約翰·威廉·赫爾頓—聖安東尼奧河自然公園（{{lang|en|John William Helton-San Antonio River Nature Park}}）位於{{tsl|en|Calaveras, Texas|卡拉維拉斯 (德克薩斯州)|卡拉維拉斯}}，佔地0.4平方公里（98英畝），由聖安東尼奧河管理局負責日常管理<ref name="JWH_Park">{{Cite web |url = https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/parks-trails/john-william-helton-san-antonio-river-nature-park |title = John William Helton-San Antonio River Nature Park |author = San Antonio River Authority |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-12 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201021043911/https://www.sariverauthority.org/be-river-proud/parks-trails/john-william-helton-san-antonio-river-nature-park |archivedate = 2020-10-21}}</ref>。園內設有步道、自然教育徑、足球場及籃球場等設施，公眾亦可進行遠足、騎[[BMX|BMX]]及[[登山車|山地單車]]、露營、划船等活動<ref name="JWH_Park"/>。{{tsl|en|Goliad State Park and Historic Site|戈利亞德州立公園及歷史遺址}}位於[[戈利亚德_(得克萨斯州)|戈利亞德]]南部，佔地1.12平方公里（276英畝），由{{tsl|en|Texas Parks and Wildlife Department|德州公園及野生動物部}}管理<ref name="Goliad State Park">{{Cite web |url = https://tpwd.texas.gov/state-parks/goliad |title = Goliad State Park & Historic Site |author = Texas Parks and Wildlife Department |publisher = State of Texas |language = en |accessdate = 2021-02-12 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20210127125834/https://tpwd.texas.gov/state-parks/goliad |archivedate = 2021-01-27}}</ref>。公園覆蓋多個歷史景點，包括經修復的埃斯皮里圖桑托傳教站（{{lang|en|Mission Espiritu Santo}}）、{{tsl|en|Mission Nuestra Señora del Rosario|羅薩里奧聖母傳教站}}廢墟、紀念{{tsl|en|James Fannin|詹姆斯·范寧}}及其餘{{tsl|en|Goliad massacre|戈利亞德大屠殺}}遇難者的范寧紀念碑等<ref name="Goliad State Park"/>。另外，公眾亦可在園內進行露營、釣魚、劃獨木舟及皮划艇、觀鳥等休閒活動<ref name="Goliad State Park"/>。

